Very shortsighted article. User experience sells devices, not specs. Blackberry was dying because they refused to let go of their dated OS, now they have adopted a better one with Google. It will be a slow come back though. People were writing the same nonsense about the Microsoft Surface three years ago. So Microsoft turfed RT and switched to Windows 10. Now that hybrid device is not only dominating, but has caused a shift in design over the rest of the tablet/laptop market.

Adriana Gambardella Parascandolo I too came here when I was 5, yet I sympathize because I remember the hardships that my parents had to go through. It's sad that you have put yourself on a pedestal and believe yourself to be above others who are simply trying to live a better life. Most of these people come from countries that subject them to terrible conditions. I have nothing against deporting criminals who committed violent crimes, but the lack of empathy toward other human beings whose only crime was to cross a border (whether crossing the actual border or overstaying their time through a visa) is what is truly troubling. Illegal immigrants and permanent residents are all afraid. To be clear, the vetting process and pathway to citizenship was much simpler back in the day.
